14/10/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Deputy Prime Minister for European Integration Vasko Naumovski said on Wednesday (October 13th) that Macedonia would welcome EU assistance in resolving the long-standing name dispute with Greece.
"All EU institutions in charge of implementing joint foreign security policy and the EU enlargement process are familiar with the name talks.
If they contribute to finding a solution ...
we will be grateful," Naumovski said.
Meanwhile, local media reported that EU President Herman Van Rompuy plans to visit Macedonia next week.
He'll be discussing the upcoming European Commission progress report on the EU integration process, as well as efforts to settle the name dispute.
(Deutsche Welle, Makfax, A1, MIA, Alsat M - 13/10/10)
